Yen Weakens After Finance Minister Noda Signals Readiness to Stem Advance

-- B y   B e n j a m i n   P u r v i s
-- 
2011-08-14T21:52:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-14/yen-weakens-after-finance-minister-noda-signals-readiness-to-stem-advance.html
The yen weakened against 15 of its
most-traded peers after Finance Minister  Yoshihiko Noda  said
he’s ready to intervene in the market again to stem an advance
in Japan’s currency that risks slowing an economic recovery.  The yen fell 0.3 percent to 109.63 per euro as of 6:48 a.m.
in Tokyo and declined to 76.88 against the dollar from 76.71 on
Aug. 12 in  New York .  The dollar traded at $1.4261 against the euro from $1.4248
last week.  The Swiss franc fell 0.6 percent to 78.32 centimes per U.S.
dollar and declined 0.8 percent to 1.1173 against the euro.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Purvis in Sydney at 
